class:: CutOSC
summary:: BBCut2 OSC output
categories:: Libraries>BBCut
related:: Overviews/BBCut

description::

A class to trace the state of cutsynths as they render algorithmically determined cuts. The cut information is sent via OSC to the NetAddr object specified as the third creation argument. Time stamped scheduling with latency guarantees accurate sync. 

examples::

code::

~fredrik=NetAddr("169.254.29.94", 9999);


(
var sf, clock, synth;

s=Server.default;

clock= ExternalClock(TempoClock(2.1)).play; 
        
Routine.run({

sf= BBCutBuffer("/Volumes/data/audio/toanalyse/reedham.wav",128);

s.sync;

BBCut2(CutBuf2(sf,1.0).trace_(CutOSC(1,0.0,~fredrik)), ChooseCutProc(1.0,2)).play(clock);

});

)





//showing all subevents generated by a CutBuf3
